# Matex MCP Server Conventions

## Tool Naming Convention
Tools follow `<verb>_<noun>` within each server's namespace, registered on the MCP server:
```
// auth-mcp
register, verify_email, verify_phone, login, logout, refresh_token, reset_password, enable_mfa

// listing-mcp
create_listing, update_listing, upload_images, set_pricing, publish_listing, get_listing, get_my_listings

// bidding-mcp
place_bid, set_proxy_bid, retract_bid, get_current_bids, submit_bid_deposit

// escrow-mcp
create_escrow, hold_funds, release_funds, freeze_funds, partial_release, refund, adjust_commission

// dispute-mcp
file_dispute, submit_evidence, propose_settlement, accept_settlement, escalate, render_decision, update_pis_score

// admin-mcp
manage_user, moderate_listing, review_kyc, configure_commission, get_audit_log, system_health
```

## Every Tool Must Audit Log
Every MCP tool call MUST write to `log_mcp.audit_log` via the `log-mcp` server — never directly. Use the interceptor pattern in the MCP server base class.

```typescript
// Tool handler template
async function handleTool(name: string, input: unknown, context: ToolContext) {
  const start = Date.now();
  try {
    const result = await executeToolLogic(name, input, context);
    await logMcp.logToolCall({ server: SERVER_NAME, tool: name, user_id: context.userId,
      action: name, input_hash: sha256(JSON.stringify(input)),
      output_summary: 'success', success: true, duration_ms: Date.now() - start });
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    await logMcp.logToolCall({ ..., success: false, error_message: String(error) });
    throw error;
  }
}
```

## Event Naming Convention
All events follow: `{server}.{entity}.{action}`

### Complete Event Catalog (with Critical flags)
| Server | Events | Critical? |
|---|---|---|
| `auth-mcp` | `auth.user.registered`, `auth.user.logged_in`, `auth.user.password_reset`, `auth.mfa.enabled` | No |
| `kyc-mcp` | `kyc.verification.completed`, `kyc.verification.expired`, `kyc.pep_match.detected` | Yes (PEP match) |
| `listing-mcp` | `listing.listing.created`, `listing.listing.published`, `listing.listing.sold`, `listing.listing.expired` | No |
| `bidding-mcp` | `bidding.bid.placed`, `bidding.bid.outbid`, `bidding.bid.won`, `bidding.suspicious_activity` | Yes (suspicious) |
| `auction-mcp` | `auction.auction.started`, `auction.lot.opened`, `auction.lot.sold`, `auction.auction.ended` | No |
| `inspection-mcp` | `inspection.inspection.completed`, `inspection.weight_discrepancy.detected`, `inspection.inspection.failed` | Yes (discrepancy, failed) |
| `escrow-mcp` | `escrow.escrow.created`, `escrow.funds.held`, `escrow.funds.released`, `escrow.escrow.frozen`, `escrow.funds.refunded` | Yes (all) |
| `payments-mcp` | `payments.payment.completed`, `payments.payment.failed`, `payments.payment.refunded`, `payments.payout.sent` | Yes (all) |
| `dispute-mcp` | `dispute.dispute.created`, `dispute.dispute.escalated`, `dispute.dispute.resolved`, `dispute.penalty.applied` | Yes (all) |
| `logistics-mcp` | `logistics.shipment.booked`, `logistics.shipment.picked_up`, `logistics.shipment.delivered`, `logistics.shipment.delayed` | No |
| `contracts-mcp` | `contracts.contract.activated`, `contracts.order.triggered`, `contracts.contract.terminated`, `contracts.contract.breached` | Yes (breach) |
| `admin-mcp` | `admin.user.suspended`, `admin.user.banned`, `admin.config.changed` | Yes (all) |

`log-mcp` subscribes to **ALL** events on the bus without exception.
Critical events trigger immediate real-time alerting via Datadog/Sentry AND a Slack notification to the operations team.

## KYC Level Gates
| Operation | Minimum KYC Level |
|---|---|
| View listings, search | `level_0` (no auth required) |
| Send messages, save searches, favorites | `level_1` |
| Place bids, make offers, post listings | `level_2` |
| Execute orders, receive payouts, use credit, API access | `level_3` |
| Live auctions, down payments, credit application | `level_2` |

Always validate KYC before financial operations:
```typescript
const kyc = await kycMcp.get_verification_status({ user_id });
if (KYC_LEVEL_ORDER[kyc.level] < KYC_LEVEL_ORDER[required]) {
  throw new KycInsufficientError(`${required} required`);
}
```

## RBAC + ABAC Authorization
Each tool declares its required role AND minimum KYC level AND additional conditions:
- **RBAC roles**: `buyer`, `seller`, `carrier`, `inspector`, `admin`
- **ABAC attributes**: KYC level, PIS score, credit tier, account age, account status
- Supabase RLS provides the data-layer enforcement backstop

```typescript
// Tool authorization declaration
const toolPolicy = {
  'bidding.place_bid': { roles: ['buyer'], minKycLevel: 'level_2', minPis: 50 },
  'escrow.release_funds': { roles: ['admin', 'system'], minKycLevel: 'level_3' },
  'admin.manage_user': { roles: ['admin'], minKycLevel: 'level_3' },
};
```

## Escrow Lifecycle State Machine
```
created → funds_held → (partially_released) → released
                    ↘ frozen → (released | refunded)
                    ↘ refunded
                    ↘ cancelled  (only before funds_held)
```
Always append to `escrow_mcp.escrow_timeline` at each transition. Never skip states.

## Response Shape Convention
```typescript
// Success
{ success: true, data: T, meta?: { pagination?, timing? } }

// Error — always include a structured error code
{ success: false, error: { code: string, message: string, details?: unknown } }
```

## Account Status Guard
Every authenticated tool call must check this first:
```typescript
if (user.account_status !== 'active') {
  throw new AccountNotActiveError(user.account_status);
}
```

## Notification Dispatch Pattern
After significant state changes, dispatch via `notifications-mcp.send_notification`:
```typescript
await notificationsMcp.send_notification({
  user_id: targetUserId,
  type: 'order.delivered',   // format: '<domain>.<event>'
  title: 'Your order was delivered',
  body: '...',
  channels: ['email', 'in_app'],
  priority: 'normal',
  data: { order_id: orderId },
});
```

## Anti-Manipulation (bidding-mcp)
1. Use `server_timestamp` — never trust client-provided timestamps.
2. Flag `velocity`: >5 bids same user, same listing, within 60 seconds.
3. Flag `shill_bidding`: bidder shares a company profile with the seller.
4. Write flags to `bidding_mcp.anti_manipulation_flags`.
5. `critical` severity → freeze escrow + alert `admin-mcp` immediately.

## MCP Server File Structure
```
packages/mcp-servers/<domain>-mcp/
  src/
    index.ts          — server entry point, registers tools
    tools/            — one file per tool group
    validators/       — Zod schemas for tool inputs
    services/         — business logic (calls Supabase)
    types.ts          — local domain types
  package.json
```
